<p>Sonoma Pinot Noirs typically display a beautiful garnet to ruby core with brick-orange edges in mature vintages, indicating proper cool-climate development. Chardonnays range from pale gold with green highlights (unoaked) to deeper golden hues with excellent viscosity that coats the glass—a sign of full malolactic fermentation and quality barrel aging. Cabernet Sauvignons show deep purple-black centers with concentrated extraction, while Zinfandels exhibit that characteristic inky, almost opaque darkness with purple-red rims.</p>

