<h3>Evolution Over Time</h3>
<p>Sonoma Cabernet Sauvignon transforms dramatically during cellaring. Young wines display intense cassis and eucalyptus notes with firm tannins. After 5-7 years, secondary flavors emerge—leather, tobacco, and cedar from oak integration. Peak maturity brings tertiary complexity: forest floor, graphite, and integrated fruit with silky tannins.</p>

<p>Russian River Pinot Noir evolves from bright cherry and cola to earthy mushroom and truffle notes, while maintaining its signature silky texture. The region's cool climate preserves acidity essential for graceful aging.</p>

<h3>Optimal Storage Conditions</h3>
<div class="bg-wine-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
<ul>
<li><strong>Temperature</strong>: 55-58°F consistent (Sonoma's temperature swings make controlled storage crucial)</li>
<li><strong>Humidity</strong>: 60-70% to prevent cork drying</li>
