<li><strong>Light</strong>: Complete darkness to prevent UV degradation</li>
</ul>
</div>

<h3>Aging vs. Spoilage Indicators</h3>
<p><strong>Proper aging</strong> shows clear wine with sediment formation, evolved aromatics, and balanced acidity. <strong>Spoilage signs</strong> include cloudy appearance, vinegar-like aromas, or excessive oxidation (sherry-like notes in red wines). Sonoma's high-quality corks typically maintain integrity for 15+ years when properly stored, though vintage variation affects longevity—exceptional years like 2013 and 2016 show extended aging potential.</p>

